# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok five days after former president george bush was inaugurated in #### , an official from bahrain set in motion a chain of events that allowed the texas oil company where the president 's son was a director to beat out amoco for drilling rights with huge profit potential .
# ::alignments
(s / set-02
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Bahrain"))
                  :ARG2 (o / official)
                  :time (f / former)))
      :ARG1 (c2 / chain-01
            :ARG1 (e / event
                  :ARG0-of (a / allow-01
                        :ARG1 (b / beat-out-04
                              :ARG0 (c3 / company
                                    :mod (o2 / oil)
                                    :location (s2 / state
                                          :name (n2 / name
                                                :op1 "Texas"))
                                    :ARG2-of (h2 / have-org-role-91
                                          :ARG0 (p2 / person
                                                :ARG0-of (h3 / have-rel-role-91
                                                      :ARG1 (p3 / person
                                                            :ARG0-of (h4 / have-org-role-91
                                                                  :ARG2 (p4 / president)))
                                                      :ARG2 (s3 / son)))
                                          :ARG1 (c4 / company
                                                :name (n3 / name
                                                      :op1 "Amoco"))))
                              :ARG1 (r / right-05
                                    :ARG2 (d / drill-01)
                                    :ARG1-of (p5 / profitable-02
                                          :mod (h5 / huge)))))))
      :ARG2 (m / motion)
      :time (a2 / after
            :op1 (ii / inaugurate-01
                  :ARG1 p3
                  :location (c5 / city
                        :name (n4 / name
                              :op1 "Bahrain")))
            :quant (t / temporal-quantity
                  :quant 5
                  :unit (d2 / day))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok independent experts from the united nations are to assess the impact of armed conflict on women and women 's role in peace-building and conflict resolution in rwanda , the rwanda news agency reported on friday .
# ::alignments
(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (a / agency
            :mod (n / news)
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Rwanda")))
      :ARG1 (a2 / assess-01
            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :ARG1-of (e / expert-01)
                  :ARG0-of (d / depend-01
                        :polarity -)
                  :source (n3 / nation
                        :ARG1-of (u / unite-01)))
            :ARG1 (ii / impact-01
                  :ARG0 (c2 / conflict-01
                        :ARG1-of (a3 / arm-01))
                  :ARG1 (r2 / role
                        :poss (a4 / and
                              :op1 (w / woman)
                              :op2 w)
                        :topic (a5 / and
                              :op1 (b / build-01
                                    :ARG1 (p2 / peace))
                              :op2 (r3 / resolve-01
                                    :ARG1 c2))
                        :location c)))
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (f / friday)))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok malaysia 's exports grew faster-than-expected in january , rising ##.# percent from a year ago largely due to higher shipments of palm oil and petroleum products , the trade ministry said thursday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (m / ministry
            :topic (t / trade-01))
      :ARG1 (g / grow-01
            :ARG1 (e / export-01
                  :ARG0 (c / country
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Malaysia")))
            :ARG2 (h / have-degree-91
                  :ARG1 e
                  :ARG2 (f / fast-02
                        :ARG1 e)
                  :ARG3 (m2 / more)
                  :ARG4 (t2 / thing
                        :ARG1-of (e2 / expect-01)))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :month 1)
            :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                  :ARG0 (s2 / ship-01
                        :ARG1 (a / and
                              :op1 (o / oil
                                    :mod (p / palm))
                              :op2 (p2 / product
                                    :mod (p3 / petroleum)))
                        :ARG1-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                              :ARG2 (h3 / high-02
                                    :ARG1 s2)
                              :ARG3 (m3 / more)))
                  :degree (l / large)))
      :time d
      :weekday (t3 / thursday))

                                    :op1 "Europe"))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG1 (s / say-01
            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "Bulent"
                        :op2 "Ecevit")
                  :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                        :ARG1 (c / country
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "Turkey"))
                        :ARG2 (m / minister
                              :mod (p2 / prime))))
            :ARG1 (c2 / concern-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / clash-01
                        :ARG0 (s2 / soldier
                              :mod (c4 / country
                                    :name (n5 / name
                                          :op1 "Israel")))
                        :ARG1 (p3 / person
                              :mod (c5 / country
                                    :name (n6 / name
                                          :op1 "Palestine")))
                        :mod (v / violent)
                        :time (r2 / recent))
                  :ARG1 c
                  :ARG1-of (s3 / serious-02)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (s4 / saturday)))

# ::id 5 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the israeli army voiced regret saturday for the death of a ##-year-old palestinian child , killed by israeli troops in the northern west bank on saturday .
# ::alignments
(v / voice-01
      :ARG0 (a / army
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Israel")))
      :ARG1 (r / regret-01
            :ARG0 a
            :ARG1 (d / die-01
                  :ARG1 (c2 / child
                        :mod (c3 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Palestine"))
                        :age (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit (y / year))
                        :ARG1-of (k / kill-01
                              :ARG0 (t2 / troop
                                    :mod c)
                              :location (c4 / country-region
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Northern"
                                          :op2 "West"
                                          :op3 "Bank"))
                              :time (d2 / date-entity
                                    :weekday (s / saturday)
                                    :time-of v))))))

# ::id 7 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok india marked the ##th anniversary of the day it gave itself a democratic constitution monday with a combination of pageantry and a display of its military strength .

            :topic (d / day
                  :time-of (g / give-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (c2 / constitution
                              :mod (d2 / democracy))
                        :ARG2 c
                        :time (d3 / date-entity
                              :weekday (m2 / monday)))))
      :manner (c3 / combine-01
            :ARG1 (p / pageantry)
            :ARG2 (d4 / display-01
                  :ARG1 (s / strong-02
                        :ARG1 c
                        :mod (m3 / military)))))

      :ARG3 (d3 / disease

# ::alignments
(a / and
      :op1 (l / look-up-05
            :ARG0 (p / person
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Patrick"
                        :op2 "O'malley")
                  :ARG0-of (g / guard-01
                        :ARG1 (s / security))
                  :age (t / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (y / year)))
            :ARG1 (t2 / television)
            :time (d / deliver-01
                  :ARG0 (p2 / person
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Clinton")
                        :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                              :ARG2 (p3 / president)))
                  :ARG1 (m / message-01
                        :ARG0 p2
                        :ARG1 (s2 / state
                              :mod (u / union)))))
      :op2 (f / find-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (n3 / nod-01
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1 (a2 / approve-01
                        :ARG1 p)
                  :concession (e / even-when
                        :op1 p)))
      :location (s3 / shop
            :mod (c / coffee)
            :mod (s4 / small)))

(s / stress-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Suleyman"
                  :op2 "Demirel")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Turkey"))
                  :ARG2 (p2 / president)))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (ii / important-01
                  :ARG1 (r / relation-03
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG2 (c2 / country
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Russia"))))
            :op2 (d / develop-02
                  :ARG1 (f / friendship
                        :ARG1-of (e / exist-01)
                        :mod (b / between
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 c2))
                  :mod (f2 / further)))
      :time (t / today))
